Assignment name  : wdmatch
Expected files   : wdmatch.c
Allowed functions: write
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Write a program that takes two strings and displays every character from the
first string that also exists somewhere in the second string, in the same order
as they appear in the first string.

Each matching character must be written once when it is found in the second
string.

The output must be followed by a newline.

If the number of parameters is not 2, the program displays nothing.

Examples:

$> ./wdmatch "abc" "zabx" | cat -e
ab$
$> ./wdmatch "hello" "world" | cat -e
lo$
$> ./wdmatch "1337" "42" | cat -e
$
$> ./wdmatch | cat -e
$```
